ePadInk - Sample files

The following files have been installed -- in some cases they have been included as source form only and cannot be built without major modification:

NameBuilds?Description
test.cppNoSource-code only sample showing how to call IWedge interface.
mfc-demoYesBuilt using MSVC++ v6.0. Shows how to use MFC/C++ to connect to a service provider and obtain data from a device.
vb-demoYesSimple visual-basic 6.0 demo using gIIEPad component to connect up to a generic device and obtain data into visual basic. Note that this does not include anything other than generic device access and as such will work with serial ePad, USB ePad as well as ePad Ink (and future products). However it may not use all of the features of newer products.
